parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning seatbelts can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as they may not provide adequate restraint or protection to the occupants.
symptoms: The seatbelt fails to engage or latch properly
the seatbelt becomes unlatched on its own
the seatbelt does not retract properly
the seatbelt bolt separates from the body frame upon impact
the seatbelt fails to release during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Seatbelts that do not retract properly can cause inconvenience, discomfort, and potentially lead to accidents if the belts become jammed or tangled.
symptoms: The front lap/shoulder belts do not retract properly when closing the door
the belt gets jammed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seatbelt latch can cause the belt to become unlatched during normal driving conditions, leading to a loss of protection in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The driver's and passenger side seatbelt becomes unlatched on its own.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seatbelt anchor can cause the belt to separate from the body frame upon impact, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seatbelt bolt separates from the body frame upon impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Control Arm Support Rust and Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and potential failure of the control arm support can cause the control arm to break loose, leading to loss of steering control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Uncontrollable front end
erratic steering control
rusted control arm hooks
and potential breakage of the control arm support.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joint can cause the axle to detach, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Broken bolt holding the ball joint
axle detachment
transmission fluid leak
and wheel damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front struts can cause uneven tire wear, noise, and vibration, leading to reduced vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: Tires cupping
noise from front struts
and leaking front struts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearing can cause noise, vibration, and potentially lead to wheel damage or loss of control, which can result in accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Noise from the right rear wheel bearing
wheel bearing falling apart
and repeated replacement of the wheel bearing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the inside door handles can cause inconvenience and difficulty in entering or exiting the vehicle, potentially leading to safety issues in emergency situations.
symptoms: Inside door handles break or fail to function
doors stick in cold weather
rubber pulling away from the door causes the dome light to stay on when the door is closed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the weather strip on the driver's door can cause the door to stick in cold weather, leading to inconvenience and potential safety issues.
symptoms: Door sticks in cold weather
weather strip needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the convertible top can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to accidents or injuries due to obstructed vision.
symptoms: Convertible top flies open while driving
ripping out the back window and bending the inside bars.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood can cause obstructed vision and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Hood flies up while driving
causing blocked vision.
